headline: The Latest Alternative Jobs Data Point to a Rough January
summary: A growing number of reports from private data sources are pointing in the same direction: The labor market started the new year poorly.  The U.S. economy likely lost more than 13,000 jobs in January, Revelio Labs estimated.

headline: January Sees Surge in Layoff Plans, Outplacement Firm Says
summary: U.S. job-cut announcements surged in January, according to outplacement firm Challenger, Gray & Christmas.  The firm counted 108,435 announced job cuts last month.   That was up sharply from the roughly 35,500 job cuts announced in December and 49,800 in January 2025.

headline: Gold rises over 1% as geopolitical, economic tensions lift precious metals
summary: Feb 5 (Reuters) - Gold climbed more than 1% on Thursday, hovering near one-week highs, as geopolitical and economic tensions continued to bolster prices, while silver and palladium also posted gains.
